Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, fry the @British beef mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiling water into a #saucepan{} with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.

Boil the @basmati rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain, pop back in the saucepan and cover.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%carton}.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g} to the beef. Cook, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the beef chilli.

Drizzle over the @soured cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!